Roadmap to learning GIT

Day 1:

    Install Git: sudo apt-get update and sudo apt-get install git
    Learn about version control and what Git is
    Create a GitHub account if you don't have one yet
    Watch this video to get a general understanding of what Git is and how it works: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SWYqp7iY_Tc

Day 2:

    Configure Git settings
    Learn basic Git commands: git init, git add, git commit, git status
    Watch this video to learn more about configuring Git and basic commands: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HVsySz-h9r4

Day 3:

    Learn about Git branches
    Create and switch between branches
    Watch this video to learn about Git branches: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XYLGnvFzF6s

Day 4:

    Learn about remote repositories
    Add a remote repository and push changes to it
    Watch this video to learn about remote repositories: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5KjapFQNxUo

Day 5:

    Learn about Git pull requests
    Create a pull request and merge it
    Watch this video to learn about pull requests: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_NrSWLQsDL4

Day 6:

    Learn about Git conflicts and how to resolve them
    Watch this video to learn about Git conflicts: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C6WM5xd5w5E

Day 7:

    Learn about Git tags and releases
    Create a tag and release
    Watch this video to learn about Git tags and releases: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gmgiv9XJw20

Additional resources:

    Git documentation: https://git-scm.com/doc
    Git tutorial: https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials
    Git cheat sheet: https://education.github.com/git-cheat-sheet-education.pdf
